author: The Record
title: CDs being released Oct. 23 - Music
text:
In stores Friday: 
Buy this photo CARRIE UNDERWOOD * Carrie Underwood, "Storyteller" (Arista Nashville) — Her fifth studio album and first in almost 3 1/2 years.
* Andrea Bocelli, "Cinema" (Verve) — The Italian tenor takes on great movie themes from "Doctor Zhivago," "West Side Story" and "The Godfather," among others.
* Harry Connick Jr., "That Would Be Me" (Columbia) — Latest from the "American Idol" judge is a bit of a departure — more pop than jazz.
* 5 Seconds of Summer, "Sounds Good Feels Good" (Capitol) — Second studio album from the Australian pop punk band.
* Rod Stewart, "Another Country" (Capitol) — His 29th studio album includes "Batman Superman Spiderman," which was written about bedtime stories that he would tell his youngest son, based around the three fictional superheroes.
— From news service reports
